        <p>Oxnard's coastal exposure is more direct than Camarillo's or Thousand Oaks's. Hollywood Beach, Silverstrand, Mandalay Bay, and Oxnard Shores condos sit within blocks of the open Pacific — there's no Conejo Valley or hill range buffering the marine air. The result: refrigerator condenser coils accumulate fine salt particulate at roughly 2-3x the inland rate. Sub-Zero coils in beachfront Oxnard Shores units that we've serviced over multiple visits show inspection-cleaning intervals of 4-5 months as the realistic target — not the 8-12 month interval Sub-Zero's manual suggests for typical residential service.</p>
        <p>Range and cooktop igniters are similarly affected. Wolf and Viking burner electrodes show coastal-air corrosion patterns within 2-3 years on direct-beachfront installs. We catch these proactively during any service call — it's a cheap fix at the early stage and a no-ignition emergency at the late stage. Outdoor-adjacent appliances (BBQ grills, outdoor refrigerators, ice makers in pool cabanas) compound the issue further.</p>
        <p>Channel Islands Harbor and the marina-adjacent properties have a slightly different exposure profile — sheltered water, less direct ocean spray, but heavier humidity year-round from the harbor itself. Service intervals here run between Oxnard Shores beachfront and inland River Ridge. We adjust the maintenance recommendations based on the specific micro-climate of where the property sits.</p>
