        <p>Oxnard has a real commercial appliance footprint that most Ventura County service companies under-serve. The reasons: Oxnard is the strawberry capital of the country (one of the largest US producers, with the California Strawberry Festival every spring), the Port of Hueneme is the only deep-water commercial port between LA and SF, and major employers including Haas Automation, Seminis, Raypak, and Drum Workshop run substantial facilities here. That commercial activity means restaurants, hotels, agricultural-processing kitchens, and small-business food operations need appliance service that goes beyond residential scope.</p>
        <p><b>What we handle on the commercial side:</b> walk-in coolers and freezers (compressor service, evaporator cleaning, defrost-timer issues), commercial refrigeration including True, Beverage-Air, and Continental units in restaurants and convenience stores, commercial dishwashers from Hobart, Champion, and Jackson in restaurants near Channel Islands Harbor and Heritage Square, commercial ranges and ovens (Vulcan, Garland, Wolf commercial), ice machines for restaurants and bars (Hoshizaki, Manitowoc, Scotsman). Commercial diagnostic is $120 flat, waived with repair — $30 above the $89 residential rate to account for the heavier-equipment service complexity.</p>
        <p>For agricultural operations specifically, we don't service field equipment or process-specific industrial machinery. We do service the cold-storage refrigeration that supports strawberry packing and post-harvest holding (these are typically commercial walk-ins or reach-ins, same equipment categories we service in restaurants). For pure industrial machinery, we route customers to Quinn Company or specialty industrial service.</p>
        <p>Oxnard hospitality customers — Embassy Suites Mandalay Bay, Residence Inn Channel Islands, smaller boutique properties downtown — get the same diagnostic + repair workflow as residential, just with the commercial pricing tier. We coordinate with property managers when units need to be off-line for service.</p>
